items.name: Thomas the Tank Engine Wikia
items.title: Thomas the Tank Engine Wikia
items.headline: Take a ride on board Thomas the Tank Engine
items.desc: The Thomas the Tank Engine Wikia is a site dedicated to the world's favorite tank engine, Thomas! With over 4,000 pages and nearly 30,000 images, the wiki has extensive details on every character, episode, magazine story, book, season, and merchandise range. We cover every facet of the Thomas franchise, including the Railway Series, the Classic Series, the New Series and the CGI series. From William Middleton to Jam Filled Productions, everything Sodor-related can be found here! So climb aboard for fun times with Thomas the Tank Engine Wikia!

items.name: Thomas & Friends Wiki
items.title: Thomas & Friends Wiki
items.headline: Visit the magical Island of Sodor, the home of Thomas and his friends!
items.desc:
Thomas & Friends is a British children's television series, first broadcast on the ITV network on 4 September 1984. It is based on The Railway Series of books by the Reverend Wilbert Awdry and his son Christopher Awdry. These books deal with the adventures of a group of anthropomorphised trains and road vehicles who live on the fictional Island of Sodor. The books were based on stories Awdry told to entertain his son Christopher during his recovery from measles. Many of the stories are based on events from Awdry's personal experience.

The Railway Series is a set of story books about a railway system located on the fictional Island of Sodor. There are 42 books in the series, the first being published in 1945. Twenty-six were written by the Rev. W. (Wilbert) Awdry, up to 1972. A further 16 were written by his son, Christopher Awdry.

items.desc:
The Thomas Wooden Railway Wiki is a wiki dedicated to the the wooden trains originally made by Learning Curve from 1992 to 2011, TOMY in 2012, and currently by Fisher-Price from 2013.

We cover all the items from, the various engines to the rolling stock and buildings, plus all the various sets and specials.
